.oE
.P
.H 4 "Configuring Local Servers, Global Servers, and Clerks"
.P
.iX "Local DTS Server" "configuring"
You can configure a single machine either as a server (local or global) or
as a clerk, but not both.  To configure a local server, global server, or
clerk, type the appropriate selection number at the DTS Configuration Menu
and press <RETURN>.
.P
If you configured a local server, \*Ldce_config\*O displays:
.oS
S:****** Configuring DTS Local Server...
S:****** Waiting for node self-identity to be established...
S:****** Starting dtsd...
S:****** This node is now a DTS local server.
.oE
.P
If you configured a global server, \*Ldce_config\*O displays:
.iX "Global DTS Server" "configuring"
.oS
S:****** Configuring DTS Global Server...
S:****** Waiting for node self-identity to be established...
S:****** Starting dtsd...
S:****** This node is now a DTS global server.
.oE
.P
If you configured a Clerk, \*Ldce_config\*O displays:
.iX "DTS Clerk" "configuring"
